cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NA, cs.IT, cs.DS 

The paper proposes a deep learning architecture for non-sparse coding, which involves solving an $L_p$-norm constrained problem. This makes it likely to belong to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a novel closed-form nonlinear unit, which suggests it could be relevant to numerical analysis (cs.NA) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed architecture on simulations and tasks related to image denoising and super-resolution, indicating a potential connection to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
